closePositionsAtMarket

java.util.Hashtable closePositionsAtMarket(int accountId,
                                           int[] instruments)
                                           throws java.rmi.RemoteException
Closes several positions at market with a single request

Parameters:
accountId - account of position
instruments - list of instrument IDs
Returns:
Hashtable maps instrument ID into corresponding result object. There is a single entry in a map for each position initially requested to be closed. The result object can be one of the following two types:
  • an long primitive, which holds an ID of a newly issued close order (for successfully closed positions);
  • an OrderException structure for positions which failed to be closed.
    Note: an attempt to close is performed independently for each position, so the successful closing of some positions and failure for some others are possible, and no action is rolled back in case of a failure (no transactional integrity for the bulk close operation).
    Throws:
    java.rmi.RemoteException - in case of remote errors

    Issues parent order and contingents. Parent order can be of type: Market, Stop, Limit. Contingents can also be defined as OCO pair.

    Parameters:
    account_id -
    order_type - the type of parent order (Market, Stop, Limit)
    instrumentId - order instrumentId
    amount - order amount
    parent_operation - parent order side: buy or sell
    price - parent order reference price
    limit_operation - buy or sell side for limit part of the order
    limit_price - limit price
    stop_operation - buy or sell side for stop part of the order
    stop_price - stop price
    oco_flag - must be set to true if contingents are OCO pair
    Returns:
    id of a newly created parent order
    Throws:
    OrderException - in case of some business-level error
    java.rmi.RemoteException - in case of remote errors
